{"descriptions":[{"id":1459,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThese verbs, consisting of a \u0026ldquo;verbalizer\u0026rdquo; and a noun, constitute the majority of verbs in Standard Spoken Tibetan. The noun may be replaced by an adjective, an adverb, or an onomatopoeia. Remember that the three main verbalizers are: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to do\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to act,\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརྒྱག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to make\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to do,\u0026rdquo; and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;to send\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to do\u0026rdquo; (and their honorific equivalents).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe verbalizer may be preceded by a simple noun:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམོ་ཊ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To drive a car\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཞས་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To sing\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐད་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To call\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམེ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To set fire\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐད་རྒྱག་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To shout\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe verbalizer can also be preceded by an adjective:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐྱིད་པོ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To have fun\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྡུག་པོ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To abuse\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགའ་པོ་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To like\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་རུ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To reduce\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆེ་རུ་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To enlarge\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe verbalizer can as well be preceded by a noun compound (see \u0026ldquo;Nominal Compounds,\u0026rdquo; above):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསློབ་སྦྱོང་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To study\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྒྱུར་བཅོས་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To reform\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡར་རྒྱས་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To improve\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསེམས་གསོ་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To console\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགདན་འདྲེན་ཞུ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To invite\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eFinally, the verbalizer can as well be preceded by a doubled form (with a verb, an adverb, an adjective or an onomatopoeia):\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཀྱོམ་ཀྱོམ་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e To stir a liquid\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདཀྲུག་དཀྲུག་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To stir,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to shake\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགཟབ་གཟབ་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To be careful\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརུག་རུག་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To gather\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕུར་ཕུར་བཏང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To massage,\u0026rdquo; \u0026ldquo;to stroke\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལྷོད་ལྷོད་བྱེད་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;To relax\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:57 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:57 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}